			data: "WEBVTT\n\n00:00.082 --> 00:03.722\nStool specimens become inadequate if only one or no stool specimens were collected\n\n00:04.082 --> 00:08.476\nor the two specimens were collected less than 24 hours apart.\n\n00:08.814 --> 00:13.754\nOne of both specimens collected more than 14 days after the onset of paralysis\n\n00:14.144 --> 00:22.126\nreceived in bad condition at the lab.\n\n00:22.698 --> 00:26.962\nSo, what situations could lead to inadequate stools?\n\n00:27.798 --> 00:28.444\nOne,\n\n00:28.704 --> 00:32.396\nLate detection of the case either because the patient sought care very late\n\n00:32.812 --> 00:40.378\nor was not reported by the health care providers during the course of illness.\n\n00:41.314 --> 00:42.016\nTwo,\n\n00:42.224 --> 00:44.876\nthe late investigation of the case can also be a cause if the case was reported in time\n\n00:45.140 --> 00:47.038\nbut timely investigation and stool collection could not be done.\n\n00:47.532 --> 00:48.260\nThree,\n\n00:48.598 --> 00:54.708\nthe case died before one or both specimens could be collected\n\n00:55.202 --> 00:57.880\nor was lost to follow up\n\n00:58.244 --> 00:59.934\nor because the AFP case had constipation.\n\n01:01.078 --> 01:01.728\nFour,\n\n01:02.092 --> 01:05.914\nthe specimens were improperly collected or packaged leading to,\n\n01:06.382 --> 01:08.176\nfor example, leakages.\n\n01:09.394 --> 01:10.044\nFive,\n\n01:10.256 --> 01:11.530\nthe reverse cold chain was poorly maintained.\n\n01:11.992 --> 01:16.672\nAll these are examples of situations that will lead to the inadequacy of the specimens\n\n01:17.354 --> 01:21.306\nand will jeopardize the lab\'s ability to detect the polio virus if it is in the stool.\n\n01:22.082 --> 01:36.070\nIn other words, negative lab results in such cases will not rule out the polio virus as the cause of paralysis.\n\n01:36.746 --> 01:42.024\nIn the case of inadequate specimens from an AFP case, we will have to do contact sampling\n\n01:42.444 --> 01:45.772\nwhich will be explained later in this lesson.\n\n"
